column1: Metropolitan area core: primary flow within an urbanized area of 50000 and greater
Metropolitan area high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to a urbanized area of 50000 and greater
Metropolitan area low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to a urbanized area of 50000 and greater
Micropolitan area core: primary flow within an urban cluster of 10000 to 49999
Micropolitan high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to a urban cluster of 10000 to 49999
Micropolitan low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to a urban cluster of 10000 to 49999
Rural areas: primary flow to a tract outside a urbanized area of 50000 and greater or UC
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to a larger urbanized area of 50000 and greater
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to a urban cluster of 10000 to 49999
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to a urban cluster of 2500 to 9999
Secondary flow 30% to <50% to a urbanized area of 50000 and greater
Small town core: primary flow within an urban cluster of 2500 to 9999
Small town high commuting: primary flow 30% or more to a urban cluster of 2500 to 9999
Small town low commuting: primary flow 10% to <30% to a urban cluster of 2500 to 9999
